<% content_for :title, "About" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "About Logister, a free bug capture and triage tool for Ruby on Rails applications." %>
<% content_for :canonical_path, about_path %>
<% content_for :og_type, "article" %>
<% content_for :json_ld, json_ld({
  "@context" => "https://schema.org",
  "@type" => "AboutPage",
  "name" => "About Logister",
  "url" => "#{request.base_url}#{about_path}",
  "description" => "About Logister and its Rails-focused bug capture workflow."
}) %>

<section class="card">
  <h1>About Logister</h1>
  <p class="muted">
    Logister is a bug capture and triage tool focused on Ruby on Rails apps.
    Our goal is to make production errors easier to understand and fix, with
    minimal setup through the <code>logister-ruby</code> gem.
  </p>
  <p class="muted">
    Today, Logister supports error and metric ingestion, grouped issue inboxes,
    request-level context, and team-friendly project access controls. The service
    is currently free while we continue building the platform.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Logister is open source and self-hostable.
    Source code: <a href="https://github.com/taimoorq/logister" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github.com/taimoorq/logister</a>.
    Rails gem: <a href="https://github.com/taimoorq/logister-ruby" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github.com/taimoorq/logister-ruby</a>.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    For setup, infrastructure, and production deployment steps, follow the README in the repository.
  </p>

  <h2>Self-host stack</h2>
  <p class="muted">
    Logister runs on Ruby on Rails (Puma) with PostgreSQL and Redis/Sidekiq,
    plus optional ClickHouse for analytics and optional Turnstile + SendGrid integrations.
  </p>

  <h2>Operator-provided configuration</h2>
  <p class="muted">
    Production operators should provide <code>RAILS_MASTER_KEY</code>,
    <code>DATABASE_URL</code>, <code>REDIS_URL</code>, and
    <code>LOGISTER_ADMIN_EMAILS</code> at minimum, with optional email/analytics/security
    variables depending on deployment needs.
  </p>
</section>
